thread.title: ‘Cute Counts for a Lot’ at the Westminster Dog Show

author: Laura Kusisto
title: ‘Cute Counts for a Lot’ at the Westminster Dog Show
text:
Any sport that judges contestants on their grooming as much as their performance can easily be dismissed as a relic. But on Tuesday evening, a group of seven immaculately coiffed and charismatic finalists wowed a crowd of thousands with a series of impressive maneuvers, proving that in this ruff competition movie-star looks can only get you so far.
The winner of the 142nd annual Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show at Madison Square Garden was a Bichon Frise named Flynn—formally named Grand Champion Belle Creek’s All I Care About...
